<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-02-01T13:32:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-02-01T13:32:00-05:00" n="240" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.002/52: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Maginnis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                        Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-02-01T14:00:00-04:32"><hi rend="italic">February 1,
                                        1921—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>15. …</p>
                        <p>Your 20 [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>], January 31st. Situation tranquil and
                            unless something unforeseen occurs, would recommend that recognition
                            should be extended next week after carnival.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Maginnis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>